   Newsweek   Is Now History 

The  liberal Newsweek Magazine is going out of business but not  before it attacks the President. Wonderful story!

Newsweek COVER!!! It is their last cover before they  fold. Also read the article at the end. AMAZING!!!

Finally, Matt Patterson and Newsweek speak out about  Obama. This is timely and tough. As many of you know,  Newsweek has a reputation for being extremely liberal. The  fact that their editor saw fit to print the following  article about Obama and the one that appears in the latest  Newsweek, makes this a truly amazing event, and a news  story in and of itself. At last, the truth about our  President and his Agenda are starting to trickle through  the protective wall built around him by the liberal  media...

By  :  Matt  Patterson
(Newsweek  Columnist - Opinion Writer)

Years  from now, historians may regard the 2008 election of  Barack Obama as an inscrutable and phenomenon, the result  of a baffling breed of mass hysteria akin perhaps to the  witch craze of the Middle Ages. How, they will wonder, did  a man so devoid of professional accomplishment beguile so  many into thinking he could manage the world's largest  economy, direct the world's most powerful military,  execute the world's most consequential job?
Imagine  a future historian examining Obama's pre-presidential  life: ushered into and through the Ivy League, despite  unremarkable grades and test scores along the way; a cushy  non-job as a "community organizer;" a brief career as a  state legislator devoid of legislative achievement (and in  fact nearly devoid of his attention, less often did he  vote "present"); and finally an unaccomplished single term  in the United States Senate, the entirety of which was  devoted to his presidential ambitions.

He  left no academic legacy in academia, authored no signature  legislation as a legislator. And then there is the matter  of his troubling associations: the white-hating,  America-loathing preacher who for decades served as  Obama's "spiritual mentor;" a real-life, actual terrorist  who served as Obama's colleague and political sponsor. It  is easy to imagine a future historian looking at it all  and asking: how on Earth was such a man elected president?  There is no evidence that he ever attended or worked for  any university or that he ever sat for the Illinois bar.  We have no documentation for any of his claims. He may  well be the greatest hoax in history.Not  content to wait for history, the incomparable Norman  Podhoretz addressed the question recently in the Wall  Street Journal: To be sure, no white candidate who had  close associations with an outspoken hater of  America like  Jeremiah Wright and an unrepentant terrorist like Bill  Ayers, would have lasted a single day. But because Mr.  Obama was black, and therefore entitled in the eyes of  liberal Dom to have hung  out with protesters against  various American injustices, even if they were 'a bit'  extreme, he was given a pass. Let that Sink  in: Obama was given a pass - held to a lower standard  because of the color of his skin.  Podhoretz  continues: And in any case, what did such ancient history  matter when he was also so articulate and elegant and (as  he himself had said) "non-threatening," all of which gave  him a fighting chance to become the first black president  and thereby to lay the curse of racism to rest? Podhoretz  puts his finger, I think, on the animating pulse of the  Obama phenomenon - affirmative action. Not in the legal  sense, of course. But certainly in the motivating  sentiment behind all affirmative action laws and  regulations, which are designed primarily to make white  people, and especially white liberals, feel good about  themselves. Unfortunately, minorities often suffer so that  whites can pat themselves on the back.

Liberals  routinely admit minorities to schools for which they are  not qualified, yet take no responsibility for the  inevitable poor performance and high drop-out rates which  follow. Liberals don't care if these minority students  fail; liberals aren't around to witness the  emotional devastation and deflated self-esteem  resulting from the racist policy that is affirmative  action. Yes, racist. Holding someone to a separate  standard merely because of the color of his skin - that's  affirmative action in a nutshell, and if that isn't  racism, then nothing is. And that is what  America did to Obama. True, Obama himself was  never troubled by his lack of achievements, but why would  he be? As many have noted, Obama was told he was good  enough for  Columbia despite undistinguished grades at  Occidental; he was told he was good enough for the US  Senate despite a mediocre record in  Illinois ; he was told he was good enough to be president despite no record at  all in the Senate. All his life, every step of the way,  Obama was told he was good enough for the next step, in spite of ample evidence to the contrary.

What  could this breed if not the sort of empty narcissism on display every time Obama speaks? In 2008, many who agreed that he lacked executive qualifications nonetheless raved  about Obama's oratory skills, intellect, and cool  character. Those people - conservatives included - ought now to be deeply embarrassed. The man thinks and speaks in  the hoariest of clichés, and that's when he has his Teleprompters in front of him; when the prompter is absent  he can barely think or speak at all. Not one original idea has ever issued from his mouth - it's all warmed-over Marxism of the kind that has failed over and over again for 100 years. (An example is his 2012 campaign speeches  which are almost word for word his 2008 speeches) And what  about his character? Obama is constantly blaming anything  and everything else for his troubles. Bush did it; it was  bad luck; I inherited this mess. Remember, he wanted the job, campaigned for the task. It is embarrassing to see a  president so willing to advertise his own powerless-ness, so comfortable with his own incompetence. (The other day he actually came out and said no one could have done anything to get our economy and country back on track).  But really, what were we to expect? The man has never been responsible for anything, so how do we expect him to act  responsibly?
In short: our president is a small-minded  man, with neither the temperament nor the intellect to handle his job. When you understand that, and only when you understand that, will the current erosion of liberty and prosperity make sense. It could not have gone otherwise with such an impostor in the Oval Office.

PROOF (with links):

TRUMP AIRLINES - In October 1988, Donald Trump threw his wallet into the airline business by purchasing Eastern Air Shuttle, a service that for 27 years had run hourly flights between Boston, New York City and Washington, D.C. For roughly $365 million, Trump got a fleet of 17 Boeing 727s, landing facilities in each of the three cities and the right to paint his name on an airplane. But his gamble was a bust. A lack of increased interest from customers combined with high pre–Gulf War fuel prices meant the shuttle never turned a profit. The high debt forced Trump to default on his loans, and ownership of the company was turned over to creditors. The Trump Shuttle ceased to exist in 1992.

TRUMP CASINOS - Donald Trump's gambles don't always go as planned. Especially when that gamble is gambling itself. In February 2009, Trump Entertainment Resorts Inc. filed for Chapter 11 bankruptcy protection for the third time in a row — an extremely rare feat in American business. The casino company, founded in the 1980s, runs the Taj Mahal, the Trump Plaza and the Trump Marina. Trump defended himself by distancing himself from the company, though he owned 28% of its stock. "Other than the fact that it has my name on it — which I'm not thrilled about — I have nothing to do with the company," he said. He resigned from Trump Entertainment soon after that third filing, but in August of that year he, and an affiliate of Beal Bank Nevada, agreed to buy the company for $100 million. 

TRUMP MARRIAGES - Donald Trump's life in the bedroom has been messy at best. The real estate magnate married his first wife, Ivana, in 1977, but things got rocky after Trump's affair with actress Marla Maples surfaced in New York City tabloids. "You bitch, leave my husband alone!" Ivana told Maples on a ski trip in Aspen, Colo. Ivana's warning fell on deaf ears, and in 1992, Trump left her with a reported $25 million settlement and married his mistress one year later. His marriage to Maples was even shorter-lived, and the couple divorced in 1999. These days, Trump is married to Slovenian supermodel Melania Knauss. 

TRUMP MORTGAGE - In April 2006, Trump announced that, after years in the real estate business, he was launching a mortgage company. He held a glitzy press conference at which his son Donald Jr. predicted that Trump Mortgage would soon be the nation's No. 1 home-loan lender. Trump told CNBC, "Who knows more about financing than me?" Apparently, plenty. Within a year and a half, Trump Mortgage had closed shop. The would-be lending powerhouse was done in by timing (the housing market cratered in 2007) and ironically enough, given Trump's Apprentice TV show, poor hiring. The executive Trump selected to run his loan company, E.J. Ridings, claimed to have been a top executive at a prestigious investment bank. In reality, Ridings' highest role on Wall Street was as a registered broker, a position he held for a mere six days.

TRUMP UNIVERSITY - They hoped to get rich off real estate, so they enrolled in Donald Trump’s University to learn the tricks of the trade, some of them maxing out their credit cards to pay tens of thousands of dollars for insider knowledge they believed could make them wealthy.

Do you remember Trump University? Probably not — founded in 2005, it didn’t really catch on. And one big reason it didn’t catch on is because it was a total scam, say former students in complaints that were filed to the Federal Trade Commission and were unearthed by a Freedom of Information Act recently requested by Gizmodo.

“I want my $35,000+ back. All I got was books that I could have gotten from the library that could guide me better then Trump’s class did." Another grievance describes a strategy reminiscent of Scientology. After paying $1,495 for a three-day seminar, which provided information freely available on Zillow, “attendees were told that unless they purchased additional products (software; individual coaching) they would not succeed,” the complaint states.

In 2013, the New York Attorney General’s office filed a $40 million lawsuit against the former reality star and current Republican presidential candidate for failing to impart the promised real estate education on 5,000 students and subjecting prospective students to high-pressure sales tactics. In April 2015, a judge ruled that Trump was indeed personally responsible and that the matter would go to trial. A class-action suit against Trump related to Trump University is also pending.

TRUMP VODKA - Trump vodka was introduced in 2006 to much fanfare. At the time, Trump predicted the T&T (Trump and Tonic) would become the most requested drink in America. On Larry King Live, he said he got into the vodka business to outdo his friends at Grey Goose. Ten years later, Grey Goose is still on top shelves throughout the country. As for Trump vodka? Yeah, we'd never heard of it either. The New York City blog Gothamist reported the vodka stopped production "because the company failed to meet the threshold requirements." In 2011, Trump's company filed an injunction to prevent an ISRAELI company from selling Trump vodka without his consent or authorization. Meaning the Donald stopped the only people in world who wanted to drink his vodka from doing so.

CHINA CONNECTION - "The problem with our country is we don't manufacture anything anymore," Donald Trump told Fox News recently. "The stuff that's been sent over from China," he complained, "falls apart after a year and a half. It's crap." That very same Donald Trump has his own line of clothing, and it's made in ... China. (OK, OK — not all of it. Salon, which reported this intriguing, head-scratching fact, notes that some of his apparel is from MEXICO and Bangladesh.)

BANKRUPTCIES - Donald Trump brags about how well his businesses have fared. Yet, no major U.S. company has filed for Chapter 11 more than Trump's casino empire in the last 30 years[*].

In 1990, the banking institutions that backed his real estate investments had to bail him out with a $65 million "rescue package" that contained new loans and credit. But it wasn't enough, and in 1991 the famous developer was nearly $4 billion in debt and his famous Taj Mahal casino had to file bankruptcy, [with another bankruptcy for Trump Castle Associates being filed in 1992*]. Trump's economic troubles continued through the '90s, while he was personally leveraged to nearly $1 billion. In 2004, Trump Hotels & Casino Resorts also filed for bankruptcy. In 2009, the same company (by then renamed Trump Entertainment Resorts Inc.) filed for bankruptcy again.

[*] http://money.cnn.com/2015/08/31/news/companies/donald-trump-bankruptcy/index.html

When in 1964 future Director of the MS, W.Czajkowski  commenced materialization of President D.D. To actions, presented with this MOTION in separate attachments, is included the case of PULASKI CLAN, which in 1768 declared war against Russia. The upraising of Pulaskis, the Confederation of Bar, had been a precursor to the American Revolution (AR), and French as well.

Heroes of the AR, Casimir Pulaski and Thaddeus Kosciusko laid the foundation to the abolishment of slavery. Kosciusko dedicated his fortune to setting Negroes free, and to the enslaved Nation of Poland he introduced American Constitution, on May 3rd of each year celebrated by the Polish People everywhere, in this way promoting the PAX AMERICANA, invoked by President J.F. Kennedy in his famous 1993 speech. Recently the UNESCO recognized year 2017 as 200th anniversary of Kosciusko’s death.    

To commemorate  both heroes of the AR, and no less heroic participants of the US’ Reconstruction Era, Ralph Modjeski, his mother Helena and their spiritus movens Ignacy                 J. Paderewski, ever since 1986 the MS is striving for establishment of the NATIONAL MODJESKA HISTORICAL DISTRICT (NMHD), approx. 2000 acres large, with added to it 800 acres under a care of the Federal Aviation Administration on the former Marine Corps Art Station El Toro in Orange County, California, called a Habitat Preserve.
To this MS’ project might also be added 850 acres of land owed to the Pulaski Clan by the US for services rendered in the American Revolutionary Army by the Brigadier-General  C. Pulaski, other debts notwithstanding.   

The NMHD might be financed in accordance with the INVESTMENT FUND HELENA MODRZEJEWSKA  (see the attached PRTCIAC), in concurrence with the indifference of President B. Clinton of 1994, rejected by President of Poland L. Kaczynski in 2006. 

Since January 5, 2016 the MS is persuading the New Government of Poland to start a dispute with Government of the USA in order to realize the NHMD and does believe, that Hon. President B. With highest regards – Wieslaw Czajkowski.
Cc:  Hon. Andrzej Duda.

                                                        (Proposal)

Taking into consideration the real motives for establishment of an agricultural colony by Poland’s Patriots, in 1876 on the territory of the USA for the purpose of emanating the idea of American Freedom in their country, since 1796 until 1918 occupied  by Russia, Prussia and Austria, I, President, Barack Obama, do PROCLAIM, that after the year 2016, the Modjeska National Historical Landmark in Modjeska Canyon, Orange County, California, hitherto known as the Helena Modjeska Historic House and Gardens,within boundaries of homesteads own by Helena Modrzejewska/Modjeska and her husband Karol Chlapowski-Bozenta, be reverted into its previous splendor, and be further called THE MODJESKA HISTORICAL DISTRICT, perpetuating bonds existing between Polish and American Nations, and be maintained by Poland in cooperation with the USA.  

And  I do also PROCLAIM, that the land on the former Marine Corps Air Station El Toro under care of the US Department of Transportation, Federal Aviation Administration as a HABITAT PRESERVE, be cooperated with the DISTRICT, as stated.

WHY I WANT TO BE DADE COUNTY FIRST AFRICAN AMERICAN CLERK OF COURT AND COUNTY CLERK BY RUBIN YOUNG

ELECT WRITE-IN CANDIDATE RUBIN YOUNG DADE COUNTY FIRST AFRICAN AMERICAN CLERK OF COURT & COUNTY CLERK

My dearest Dade County;

Over the last 43 years, I have seen the deaths, the destruction and the devastation of many lives in this county. I have seen family members die senselessly because of a lack of respect for humanity and others self-worth.

I have seen children and families starve due to a lack of resources that should be freely given and freely received from their government.

When you have lived in communities destroyed by poverty during the day and by gun fire during the night; then you should have a basic understanding as to why I want you to Elect Write-In Candidate Rubin Young, Dade County First African American Clerk of Court and County Clerk.

We say each and everyone of us "I pledge allegiance to the Flag of the United States of America, and to the Republic for which it stands, one Nation under God, indivisible, with liberty and justice for all.”.

"For all" it means we are all our brothers and sisters keepers. We should not be treating each other differently because of "Shades of Grey" that lives on the outside of you and me. Is my red heart the same as everyone else, is my red lungs the same as everyone else, do I not bleed red blood when cut like everyone else, so why are we treating each other differently because of a so-called skin color.

I don't believe in discrimination against a person's race, gender, personal preference, political background or skin color; we are all part of a Giant humanity. A humanity that is bigger than you or I; no matter how much money you have in the bank, no matter how much education you possess, no matter how big your home, and no matter how much property you have listed in your name.

We are all God's children and we are all part of his humanity.
In a county that is more culturally diversed as Dade County, we need each other. My family in 1896, came from the Bahamas and they settled in Homestead and Coconut Grove during the time Mr. Henry Flagler starting building his railroads.

It was during a time of much prosperity and progress because we needed one another to get ahead. That is why I believe that the essential elements of our success rest in my becoming Dade County's first African American Clerk of Court and County Clerk. I want to work on behalf of people and communities neglected and abused by a system which refuses to "Let My People Go".

As a county administrator, who has the background and experience to be Mr. Clerk and make Dade County government more people oriented and accountable? I promise that there will no longer be companies in this county that discriminate against people or ethnic groups looking for work; that we will no longer have elections stolen from people deserving of a public seat; that we will no longer have elected officials and non-profit groups endorsing political candidates as mentioned in F.S. 104.061 or using their corrupt influences to sway local, state municipal and/or county elections.

We will no longer have misappropriation or diversion of taxpayer’s funds from one community or neighborhood to another, there will no longer be fraudulent foreclosures filed by attorneys without the original signer of the mortgagee signature or on the contract for legal standing, there will no longer be illegal property home value assessments, no internet auctions or property tax increases that remove homestead exemptions fraudulently in this county under my leadership, there will be no mistreatment of senior citizens living in nursing homes or assisted living neighborhoods and/or single mothers and their children living on housing assistance being discriminated.

As Dade County Clerk of Court and County Clerk, I stand will all unions in the fair negotiations of their contracts and their rights to organize.

Why I know pain and I know what disappointment feels like which should be part of the job’s qualifications.

This county must become the highest example for our children and the message that we send to them must be different than the messages of the past.

My goals are to make Dade County adhere to spending priorities as mentioned in our Home-Rule Charter. So I am asking for this opportunity as my future employers to allow me to make history and to show that Dade County is a county that believes in progress, cultural diversity and economic opportunity. We also need to finally do right by Mary L. Hill, founder of the Economic Opportunity Act of 1964, 1972, 1978 and the Community Service Act of 1974.

As a county let’s take responsibility and return this woman back into her position as the “National Regional Community Service Director” removed unlawfully by our government and let us “Free Drewery Geter” from prison for a crime that he did not commit, but due to misrepresentation by an attorney he now serves life in prison for a crime he did not commit after getting out of the United States Army where he served 10 long years.

Please join me and demand that this government “FREE DREWERY GETER” and “RESTORE MARY L. HILL as NATIONAL REGIONAL COMMUNITY SERVICE DIRECTOR”.

There will be great heartaches, strives, changes and strong differences of opinions, yet we must still stay together for all times.

Let’s also address how much more money Dade County needs in dealing with the problems of "Rising Sea Levels" which should be a priority within this county on behalf of our children.

My dearest Dade County, we must not see ourselves as many races, many cultures and/or many diverse communities; we must see ourselves as "One Beloved Community" for generations to come.

Let us make Dade County responsible for every citizen and not only by single member districts that are still part of Dade County. 

Let us become a county that is opening up doors which leads through doors of humanity for all to enter "Let My People Go".

AMEN!!!!

Every day, the nation’s law enforcement agencies at the local, state, and federal levels—including the FBI and the Drug Enforcement Administration (DEA)—use investigative resources to target the supply side in the war against drugs.

But even with numerous law enforcement successes in this area, the demand for drugs continues. And one of the more worrisome trends is a growing epidemic of prescription opiate and heroin abuse, especially among young people.

Today, in an effort to help educate students and young adults about the dangers of opioid addiction, the FBI and DEA unveiled a documentary called Chasing the Dragon: The Life of an Opiate Addict at the Newseum in Washington, D.C., before an audience of educational leaders from the region. The 45-minute film, whose title refers to the never-ending pursuit of the original or ultimate high, features stark first-person accounts told by individuals who have abused opioids or whose children have abused opioids, with tragic consequences.

“This film may be difficult to watch,” explains FBI Director James Comey, “but we hope it educates our students and young adults about the tragic consequences that come with abusing these drugs and that it will cause people to think twice before becoming its next victim.”

And according to Acting DEA Administrator Chuck Rosenberg, “The numbers are appalling—tens of thousands of Americans will die this year from drug-related deaths, and more than half of these deaths are from heroin and prescription opioid overdoses. When you get right down to brass tax, capitalism is about greed. Plain and simple. The idea of "greed is good" is at the heart of the very foundation of capitalism. It is that very concept that brought on the Great Depression of the 1930's and the Great Recession of 2008. At its very core is the principle of maximizing profits at the expense of workers; avoid paying federal income taxes, and doing anything and everything, oftentimes immoral or illegal to make a profit. Profit is more important than people; it's more important than family; it's more important than the environment.
 
I imagine all of my conservative friends heads are exploding right about now. "Oh my god, he's anti-capitalism." Nothing could be further from the truth. However, I am anti-unregulated capitalism. I reject the notion that greed is good. I don't believe in the psychosis of profits over people, families and communities that afflict the overwhelming majority of corporations in America today or the intense aversion to allowing workers to form unions and collectiveIy bargain. After all it was unions that created the greatest middle class the world has ever known.

That's why it is absolutely no coincidence that the decline of real wages and the destruction of the middle class is happening at the very same time that workforce union participation is at its lowest it has been in 3 decades. It's also no coincidence that states with a strong union presence have better wages, better benefits and better workplace safety than so called "right to work" states like Texas or Kansas. 

Over the last 30 years, wages have not kept up with worker productivity or the cost of living. And that is by no accident. It's very much an intended outcome. It's a conscience decision by corporations and CEO's to keep wages low and it's exactly what Reaganomics ("trickle down") was designed to do from the very beginning.

Working 2, 3 and sometimes 4 jobs and still not being able to make ends meet or not being able to afford to send a child to college or stay in your home after a lengthy hospital stay is not what the American dream is supposed to be about.

We can rebuild the middle class, we know how to do this. FDR gave us the blueprint after the Great Depression, but it's going to take millions of Americans, who are overwhelmingly conservative, to remove the blinders from their eyes and stop voting against their own best economic self interests. Contrary to what most poor and working class conservatives may erroneously believe, the economic interests of the super wealthy and the rest of us are not the same. 

This misguided notion that certain occupations like fast food worker; a Walmart cashier or being a janitor doesn't deserve the dignity of a living wage is exactly what CEO's who make tens of thousands of dollars an hour and Billionaires like the Koch brothers want you to believe. Is there a petition to declare support for a recess appointment to replace Scalia?

Although it seems (again) that President Obama's (sometimes maddening) MODERATION makes him resistant to this, Republican EXTREMISM creates a perfect storm for such action, since the Senate is in a 10-day recess. Here are the facts (from Instapundit):

COULD OBAMA MAKE A RECESS APPOINTMENT TO REPLACE SCALIA?: The answer appears to be “yes,” because (once again), the GOP-controlled Senate voluntarily has left itself vulnerable to the exercise of such presidential power. Article II, section 2 of the Constitution gives the President power to fill vacancies “during the recess of the Senate”:
The President shall have Power to fill up all Vacancies that may happen during the Recess of the Senate, by granting Commissions which shall expire at the End of their next Session.
There’s a lot of misinformation out there. For example, a report by Fox News mistakenly focuses on the Adjournment Clause of Article I, section 5, which merely states that neither House of Congress may adjourn for more than three days without the consent of the other. The Fox News reporter wrongly concludes:
[S]o long as both the House and Senate haven’t jointly agreed to “adjourn” for a stretch longer than three days, then there appears to be no way the president could make a recess appointment.
But the House and Senate are not operating under those circumstances right now. Both bodies of have adjourned until later this month for the President’s Day recess.
The Senate last met on Thursday. When doing so, it approved a “conditional adjournment resolution” for the Senate not to meet again until Monday, Feb. 22. The House met on Friday and at the close of business adopted the same adjournment resolution to get in sync with the Senate. The House is out until Tuesday, Feb. 23.
So, the House and Senate will not be meeting in the coming days. This is an adjournment and is not challengeable in court the way the NLRB recess appointments were because both bodies have agreed with each other to adjourn.
Whether the House of Representatives is in adjournment is irrelevant to the Recess Appointments Clause power. The only salience of the Adjournment Clause is that, in NLRB v. Noel Canning (2014), the Supreme Court looked to the Adjournment Clause as relevant evidence in its quest to ascertain a minimum period of time for determining the meaning of a “Recess of the Senate” in the Recess Appointments Clause. Specifically, the Court concluded:
The Adjournments Clause reflects the fact that a 3-day break is not a significant interruption of legislative business. As the Solicitor General says, it is constitutionally de minimis. A Senate recess that is so short that it does not require the consent of the House is not long enough to trigger the President’s recess-appointment power. . . .
If a Senate recess is so short that it does not require the consent of the House, it is too short to trigger the Recess Appointments Clause. And a recess lasting less than 10 days is presumptively too short as well.
Thus, a Senate recess of fewer than 3 days is not enough to trigger the President’s recess appointment power; the Senate’s recess must be at least ten days in duration.
So how long is the Senate’s present recess? It began on Friday, February 12, with the passage of S. Con. Res. 31 which states:
That when the Senate recesses or adjourns on any day from Thursday, February 11, 2016, through Saturday, February 20, 2016, on a motion offered pursuant to this concurrent resolution by its Majority Leader or his designee, it stand recessed or adjourned until 12:00 noon on Monday, February 22, 2016, or such other time on that day as may be specified by its Majority Leader or his designee in the motion to recess or adjourn, or until the time of any reassembly pursuant to section 2 of this concurrent resolution, whichever occurs first; . . .
Sec. 2. (A) The Majority Leader of the Senate or his designee, after concurrence with the Minority Leader of the Senate, shall notify the Members of the Senate to reassemble at such place and time as he may designate if, in his opinion, the public interest shall warrant it.
A Senate recess from February 12 (at noon) until February 22 (at noon) is a recess of exactly 10 days. Thus, under Noel Canning, the Senate is potentially in recess, and President Obama’s recess appointments power may be exercised.
Under S. Con. Res. 31, the only way to recall the Senate back into business before February 22 is with the “concurrence [of] the Minority Leader of the Senate,” Harry Reid (D-NV). Somehow I doubt Sen. Reid will grant such concurrence to reconvene, should President Obama decide to use this 10-day recess to make a recess appointment and replace Justice Scalia. But should President Obama try use this particular 10-day recess to replace Justice Scalia, the replacement would only be constitutionally permitted to serve until the end of the next session– i.e., until the end of the 1st session of the 115th Congress, which would be sometime in early January 2018. [H/T to Mike Rappaport and Casey M for noting this, as my original post referenced the end of the current session].
But there is another potential wrinkle. Specifically, the Congressional Record of February 12 shows that Senate declared that it would be in pro forma session (where a member of the Senate gavels in and gavels out every few days), declaring:
A unanimous-consent agreement was reached providing that when the Senate completes its business on Friday, February 12, 2016, it adjourn, to then convene for pro forma sessions only, with no business being conducted on the following dates and times, and that following each pro forma session, the Senate adjourn until the next pro forma session: Monday, February 15, 2016, at 11:00 a.m., and Thursday, February 18, 2016, at 9:00 a.m.; and that when the Senate adjourns on Thursday, February 18, 2016, it next convene at 3:00 p.m., on Monday, February 22, 2016, unless the Senate receives a message from the House of Representatives that it has adopted S. Con. Res. 31; and that if the Senate receives such a message, it stand adjourned until 3:00 p.m., on Monday, February 22, 2016.
Notice, however, that the pro forma status of the Senate’s recess is made conditional: “unless the Senate receives a message from the House of Representatives that it has adopted S. Con. Res. 31; and that if the Senate receives such a message, it stand [sic] adjourned until 3:00 p.m., on Monday, February 22, 2016.”
This matters because if the Senate is in pro forma session, the Noel Canning majority agreed that such pro forma sessions will block the president’s recess appointment power:
We hold that, for purposes of the Recess Appointments Clause, the Senate is in session when it says it is, provided that, under its own rules, it retains the capacity to transact Senate business.
Unfortunately for the GOP Senate, however, the GOP-controlled House agreed to S. Con. Res. 31 on February 12 without objection. This means that under the plain language of S. Con. Res 31, the Senate is “in recess”–and not in pro forma session.
If this is indeed the case, the Senate is presently in the midst of a 10-day recess (not a pro forma session), and under Noel Canning, President Obama possesses the power to make a recess appointment to the Supreme Court until noon on February 22, when the Senate comes back in session.

"Hillary Clinton is a neoliberal building on the legacy of Ronald Reagan and Bill Clinton. She doesn’t understand the pivotal role inequality plays in creating economic crisis and reducing economic growth. She has been taken in by a fundamentally right wing paradigm, and if she is elected she will continue to lead the Democratic Party down that path.

Bernie Sanders is a democratic socialist building on the legacy of Franklin Roosevelt and Lyndon Johnson. He understands that inequality is the core structural factor in economic crisis and that growth in real wages and incomes is required for robust, sustainable economic growth.

It doesn’t matter which one is more experienced, or which one’s policies are more likely to pass congress, or which one is more likely to win a general election, or which one is a man and which one is a woman. This is not about just this election, or just the next four years. This is about whether the Democratic Party is going to care about inequality for the next decade. We are making a historical decision between two distinct ideological paradigms, not a choice between flavors of popcorn. This is important. Choose carefully."
link_name: Why Bernie vs Hillary Matters More Than People Think

I believe that we're on the tipping point of something huge. It's more than just a matter of healthcare and college and wages, it's a fundamental difference in the way our country works. It's about electing someone who has respect for the people in the country that he or she is serving, someone who won't back down from what they believe in when faced with threats and bribes and power, and most importantly someone who is more than just a single person. Someone who has the support of millions of people, from every racial background, age range, and belief system. Because when enough people are united in a cause, anything is possible.

Sen. Thomas Carper of Delaware -- After homestate favorite Vice President Joe Biden declined to run, Carper issued a statement endorsing Clinton. "Nearly 15 years ago, Hillary and I were elected to the United States Senate together, and since then I've had the joy and privilege of wishing my friend a happy birthday each year on October 26th. When I called her today, I had the opportunity to deliver a unique birthday message -- that I am proud to endorse her as the next Democratic nominee for President," he said.

Sen. Bob Casey of Pennsylvania -- At a 2014 event in Philadelphia, Casey told CNN that it was too early to talk about Clinton 2016. "I'm not going to get into that," he said. status_message: i support the occupy movement

This is just a little off the beaten path for this group, and I hope y'all will indulge me just a bit for this.  It's a video I've just completed that I've been meaning to put together for some time now.  And I suspect like-minded friends like you might appreciate it.

Several years ago, I became acquainted with Bud Carter, who had been News Director at WHB in Kansas City, the AM top 40 radio station I grew up listening to.  He was News Director there in 1968 at the time of the MLK assassination and led the station's effort to cover the riots that ensued after the tragic killing.  About ten years ago, Bud gave me this tape recording of a WHB station composite he was asked to produce in 1968 for WHB Sales to demonstrate the station's award-winning news coverage of this developing story to potential advertising clients.  By simply wrapping some old WHB jingles around that composite and adding some images I found on the Kansas City Public Library's awesome website, I now offer this video as a way of preserving this important historical record.  It is with the utmost humility and respect that I share it as a small gift from me to the world in commemoration of Black History Month, 2016.  #BlackLivesMatter
link_name: 1968 Kansas City Holy Week Riots as reported by WHB News

Hello 
    One of the things that i hate about elections is people get their panties in a bunch over republicans vs democrats, or democrats vs republicans, STOP, your americans 1st and foremost, do whats best for your country, if the best candidate falls into your party of choice then great, awesome, break out the bubbly, but if they dont, then open your eyes to the matrix and still vote for that person, this is our country your talking about, not the party, we cant have bad leadership and expect to flourish as a country.  I am a veteran and not affiliated with any party, i have pride in my country despite what i see happening today, america needs leadership and we need it now more than ever.  I hope all of you are paying attention to whats happening on the outside and realize how close we are to WW3.  One mistake in Syria with Russia and that will happen, and how many of you feel confident with the competency of the leadership we have today?  Putin, Iran, China, North Korea, ISIS, they all think we're growing 'soft' - and being a vet this hurts me to admit but i agree with them, we have grown soft, our military is tired of fighting these bs conflcts with no end in sight, why are we there?  Libya, Iraq, Afghanistan, and now Syria, have we really helped any of them to become a better place or have we just made matters worse?  How did we allow Benghazi to happen?  13 hours those brave americans held out and all we could send them was a handful of security from Tripoli and a UNARMED DRONE????  I call bs, i can drive halfway across OUR country in 13 hours so do not tell me we couldnt get help to Benghazi within a few hours, UNARMED DRONE? Mind boggling, nice recruitment post for the State Dept, we'll send you to a hostile foreign land with below minimum security, sound good?  I have some cheap swamp land for sale if u think that does, lol.  Another subject I want to talk about while I have a captive audience being dazzle by me, is Mefloquine (Lariam) the anti-malaria pill that our military gave to over 100k soldiers from 1990 to about 2010, the pill that is being called the military suicide pill or the Agent Orange of our generation, the VA now reports that we're losing 22 veterans per day to suicide, thats not acceptable, we dont have the research to prove the connection to Lariam, but its strongly being considered to being suspect #1, I am trying to get Congress and Roche to investigate, we're losing too good people, good people that are suffering silently, good people that have went overseas to do their patriotic duty.  I hope you will read my petition, if you agree please sign and share it, we need to make the public aware of whats happening and whats not happening at this point, if we wait 20+ years like we did with Agent Orange then thousands of lives will have be wasted.  Scary thing is this pill was the #1 anti-malaria pill for years, and millions of people have taken it, I hope I am wrong about it but the more I learn the more it scares me, I hope it scares you too, enough that you join the petition and spread the word, this is a potential global epidemic on a massive scale.  

Thank you 　 
Jerry Weaver

I’m providing two more weapons to add to your Hillary Clinton-debunking arsenal when politely discussing her candidacy with Hillary supporters. 

1. “Hillary Says She’s Not an “Establishment” Candidate—Because She’s a Woman [Running For President]” – Slate.com headline.  This is an easy one.  Two other women have run for president, one in 2012 and one this year: Michele Bachmann and Carly Fiorina, two female bastions of non-establishment political presidential candidates if I ever saw one.  Ok, that Hillary fib has been dispensed with. 

2. “Hillary Clinton: Single-payer health care will "never, ever" happen” – CBS News online article.  This is what she is saying: Although she would be a progressive president ready to go, the Congress she will be working with will always, always be a Conservative/GOP-controlled Congress that will never, never enact a national single-payer health care system. She is admitting that although she would be a progressive president if elected, her coattails would not be long enough to a multitude of progressive Democratic politicians into Congress to pass progressive legislation. She’s announcing defeat before the battle has been started. She believes that improving and expanding the Affordable Care Act aka Obamacare—which had its genesis in the Koch-owned Heritage Foundation back in the ‘70s—is the only “progressive” way to go—and remember, she’s ready to go! Despite all her progressive talk she continues to think traditionally and regressive, that real progressive politics will never work or ever come about in the United States.  And she intends to remain in the forefront keeping a national single-payer health care system from ever progressing forward and being enacted into law. 

You’re welcome.

You are invited to a party at Merridee’s, Thursday, February 11, from 4:00 to 6:00. This is a celebration of Bill Peach’s sixth book, Main Street Philosopher: A Biography on Seven Bricks. The public is invited and friends will continue the party probably until around 8:30. I hope you can join us. 

Main Street Philosopher is a collection of essays based on Bill Peach’s fifty-two years (1951-2003) of experience as a merchant and men’s clothier on Main Street in Historic Franklin Tennessee. The “philosopher” shares stories of Main Street as it was in the 1950s and the changes that came. With a life view gained from a mid-twentieth-century upbringing in a country hollow and a small town, he writes on matters of religion and education from a philosophical and political slant.

SOCIAL PSYCHOLOGY:  --While Rubio's blunders have probably cost him the GOP nomination this week (see the on-line articles on RobotRubio and his mechanical repetitions, and out of context, of set campaign talking points, a strange sight to have seen last Friday), Mrs. Clinton's are those of Cognitive Distortions triggering errors in judgement in part as in her sense of Entitlement, one such distortion.  Her sense of entitlement includes her view of herself as paying the price through service to the country on issues such as medical care for citizens and, oddly, on her being a woman, as if that entitles anyone to any thing.  The major Feminists of the past would consider her a strange associate in the struggle for liberty and social justice on a number of fronts.
--  Progressives are less than enthusiastic about her;  as one associate notes, he strikes one as "a 1974 Republican" (which is no doubt better than being an anti-science contemporary Republican).  ----Sanders in contrast is a FDR New Deal Democrat, as Chomsky notes, as viewed by political developments within the U.S.    --- Sanders seems freer of the cognitive distortion and logical fallacy of Either-Or thinking.  He does not have a list of political enemies or record of engaging in overstatements in order to score points for his team or himself. In thinking internationally he is less limited by the fallacy of Ethnocentrism, that we are the center of what is good and true in religion, a speciality of the GOP now. 
--It might be proposed that this election will not be so much about foreign policy, or how hawkish a candidate is, but about social issues in this country, finally, including what Warren and Sanders refer to as the rigging of the economy.  Here Clinton seems tone deaf, and younger voters, thinking past the new election, see their futures under a perpetual threat from a system paying to protect the few while the many suffer economically.  Being hawkish is not a central virtue to those wishing to apply critical thinking and long-term thinking about social and economic problems, and her Sanders is the more appealing to those under thirty with college educations in particular.      A. Salmon

This is a short essay on why I support Bernie.  I hope you'll read this and consider what I have to say.   Thsnk You!

I was a Hillary supporter.  I didn't like Bernie either.  Thought he looked like a wild scientist more than presidential.  My daughters are in college and have never cared about politics.  All of a sudden I heard them having in depth political conversation about the direction this country is going.  They didn't pic him cause he has style or because he's cool.  They want him because they are tired of the wars their generation is fighting.  They're afraid of the Next War having a draft. They believe in his message.  Having been in military conflicts. w 7th Special Forces trainig Contras in Nicaragua I can empathize.  I agree wall stret is rigged. I agree banks need to be broke up the way Republican President. Teddy Rosevelt did with the first anti trust laws to break up momopolies.
I think we need a masive shake up in DC and wall street.  We need Campaign Finance reform to remove "McCain/Feingold" and "Citizens United."  I see Hillary as too close to the problem to be able to fix it.  I have trust issues.  Why wont she release the transcipts to all the speaches she gave to the banks??  Cause they love her and she thinks the banks have been midunderstood. She has Super Pacs and big$ banks financing her camoaign.  He has only individual campaign donors averaging $27.00 each.  And he's pulling in as much as her.  He has experience of 30 yrs fom Mayor to Congress to the Senate.  He knows his way around.  This election means alot to everyone. But not as much as it does to our Youth. I have to condider the welfare of my kids  It may be the most important election of our lifetime but especially theirs. WW3 is coming trust me! With a draft including women. Theres a bill in the house right now to add women to the draft.  Why if they don't expect a big war?  This election is the biggest of our lives and I have to consider my kids and the future.  Too often we live in the hear and now without thinking ahead.  Iraq is an example.  GW didnt think about the 10 yrs down the road or the power vacuum it would leave.  Bush Sr and Col. Colin Powell did.  It's why they stopped short of Bagdad in Dedert Storm and set up no fly zones that were working.  I think like a soldier.  I smell death, you never forget, I see the blood, the death of children.  I see their bodies in the street bloading. So many that they rot for days weeks before we can bury them.  The sweet sickening smell of dead bodies is everywhere.  Then theres the wide spread distruction.  The desimation of historic sights that have lived through a thousand years of war til this one.  Thousand years of history that lynks us all together gone forever.  Our kids and grand kids will never be able to see these beautiful historic sights or learn about them.  They're gone now.  War is a terrible terrible thing and too often we set here insulated from it and forget it's even going on.  Comfortable in our warm homes while the war rages on.  Then theres the war that comes home with them.  PTSD, Maimed, loss of limbs etc. It never ends for many of them.  The last war generation.  Vietnam.  Brought us kennedy and Johnson. I am going with my gut.  I'm supporting my kids.  My life is set.  I wont have to fight.  Ill be ok.  They wont and they have their whole lives ahead of them.  I dont want to see it snuffed out for a war and situstion that started on lies for wmds.  We had a right to get Bin Laden in Afghanistan. We should have stayed there and Laden would have been caught long long before. This is my oppinion.  It's why I support Bernie and I hope you will join me! Feel The Bern!!
The double standard is striking.

I see the Illinois Board of Elections has demonstrated their intellectual laziness and declared Ted Cruz a natural born citizen and did so by reiterating the Senator's lame argument of "he's a citizen because his mother was a citizen." This is the crux of Senator Cruz's premise and his argument regarding his "natural born citizen" status. It is wholly dependent on his mother's American citizenship regardless of his birth place, his father's citizenship and the reason the family was in Canada at the time of Senator Cruz's birth. I have heard the various Harvard Constitutional Law professors and their reasoning regarding the meaning of the term "natural born" as defined in English Common Law and believe it to be sufficient to put the matter to rest. But I think there is another aspect no one has addressed and it concerns the premise of the argument that citizenship is granted via perpetuity because one parent is a citizen. Let's pretend Ted Cruz never left Canada. Let's pretend he grew up there, met a nice Canadian girl and had a child. Under Senator Cruz's premise his child would also be a natural born citizen of the United States as the child would have one parent that was a natural born citizen of the U.S. (Ted Cruz) In our make believe scenario let's pretend Ted Cruz's child also never leaves Canada and grows up and marries a nice Canadian girl and they have a child. Under Senator's Cruz's premise for his argument, would that child, Ted Cruz's grandchild, not also be considered a natural born citizen of the U.S.? Here we are, three generations of the Cruz family all having been born in Canada, all having lived in Canada and all having never set foot in the U.S. and yet according to Senator Ted Cruz's premise all would be natural born citizens of the U.S. as they all had at least one parent who would be considered as a natural born citizen of the U. S. and therefore all would be eligible to be President of the United States. This is exactly what the founding fathers were trying to prevent when they included "natural born citizen" into the requirements for the office of President of the United States..

status_message:
WHEN I GET OLDER

 My name is Anthony. I’m two years old in this picture. I like to ride my big wheel, chase birds and run around in stores and hide and watch my mother lose her mind. It’s fun! I like when we go for a drive in the car and I get to tell my parents which way to turn because I have a very good sense of direction. I like cookies and candy and snacks. I have two stomachs, a food stomach and a snack stomach. My food stomach gets full quickly but my snack stomach never does. My parents don’t believe this, but they’re just stupid heads. 

 I’m older now and I want to make some friends. The kids my mom tries to hook me up with want to play with my computer (it’s really my Dad’s computer but he lets me use it) and swim in my parent’s pool, but they don’t really want to be my friends. I don’t know why. Maybe there is something wrong with me, or maybe those kids are just stupid heads. 

 I’m in middle school now and I’m going to find some friends on my own. There are some kids who smoke pot and want me to smoke pot too and be their friends. I promised my Mom I would never do drugs. Drugs are bad for you. But pot is not a drug. It’s an herb and it’s all natural, and these kids who smoke it are not stupid heads. And they want to be my friend.

 In high school I meet some new kids who might be my friends. They are all taking pain pills so I will take pain pills too so they won’t think I’m weird. They are just pills, right? They come from a doctor just like the pink stuff my mom used to give me when I was a baby and had an earache. Taking pain pills won’t hurt me and it will get me lots of new friends.

 These pain pills make me feel good and l don’t have to think about whether my friends really like me or just want to hang around me because I know where to get pot and pain pills. But boy have those pills gotten expensive.

 I’m in college now and those pain pills I need haven’t gotten any cheaper. OK, I have to take more pills then I used to, but still, it’s hard to come up with $180 every time I have to take my pills. I don’t like stealing from my family and I don’t like selling stuff on e-Bay that my friends steal and pretending to myself that I don’t know that it’s stolen, but I’ve got to have those pills.

 But there is another way. I hate needles, but Heroin is so damn cheap I guess I’m going to have to get used to them. It’s not so bad. After the first couple of times it was easy. And the heroin works even better than the pills, and OK, I shoot heroin, but I’m not an addict or anything.

 Oh my God, what a loser I am! I am a heroin addict. I’m doing it almost every day and I can’t stop. My younger self would call me a “stupid head” and he’d be right.

 The past six years have been tough. I get clean, then I relapse. Then I get clean, then I relapse. I’m in rehab again. It’s my third time and I know the drill so I know my time here is almost up. Insurance will only pay for so much time because they consider addicts losers and a waste and they try to cut you off as fast as they can. Three weeks is not enough time to learn how to deal with the cravings and all the triggers to use, but I’m really going to try to stay clean when I leave this time.

 Things are finally starting to come together for me. I still have a year to go at Penn State but I’m not sure I’m going to go back. I got a job as a salesman selling high quality food and related products and I’m really good at it. I’m also making bank. I’m saving up to get my own place and I’m thinking about maybe moving to Cali. I’m hanging around with my little brother Nick more. He’s actually pretty cool. I’m helping my Mudder by cooking diner for the fam when she works. I just got my boxer puppy from a breeder in Oklahoma. I’m calling him Caesar. He is so cute and I’m going to train him to listen to me. My best bud, Phil, is coming over tonight and we’re going to hit some bars, maybe check out a party. My legal troubles are all straightened out. My probation officer came by earlier today and drug tested me. I don’t get tested again for another week so I’m thinking maybe just one more time.

 My friend Nicole stopped by to see me today. She was at my funeral and now she’s dead too from heroin. There’s no time here in heaven, but Nicole said it’s been about a year since I died. She said my parents have become advocates for addicts and for removing the stigma of addiction and for improving addiction treatment. I think that’s a good thing. 

 She said my Dad is trying to get the insurance companies or the government to pay for longer treatment, at least ninety (90) days. I think that would help a lot of people. She said he wants to name it after me and that he started this petition on MoveOn.org http://petitions.moveon.org/sign/anthonys-act… and he wants to get as people as he can to sign and help get more people to sign by sharing it on Facebook and Twitter and by e-mailing all their friends. If I were still alive I would definitely sign it and I hope you will sign it and share it and tell all your friends to sign it and share it too.

 I have all the time in the world now and I can wait to see all my friends who do drugs. I want them to live a long, full life before we meet again. Let’s give them a real chance at recovery. Please sign the Anthony’s Act petition http://petitions.moveon.org/sign/anthonys-act….

status_message:
HRC and her campaign didn't walk away with Iowa. In realpolitik, that's a LOSS for her because Bernie jumped more than 30% while her support dropped almost the same amount.

Hillary has been a world figure and part of the political system for more than 40 years, and she ran for pres before. The Clinton machine that was formed and carried Bill into the presidency has only grown stronger during those years. 

Last summer, virtually NO ONE in this country had ever even heard of Bernie. His crowds, the record small donations, the grassroots support, and his honest and forthright approach and standing on his principles rocketed him to matching Clinton last night in the caucuses. The coin flip luck for her is a very small consolation for a woman who was sure she'd sweep Iowa back when she declared. 

All the media's declaration of her as the "winner" is just their ongoing propaganda machine. And there was absolutely no way she could have done anything other than call it a "win." She, the DNC, the Dem establishment and the media are invested in a "status quo" political system that THEY HAVE CREATED over the last 4 decades. Given their investment, they're going to bald face lie, skew numbers, revise the English language ("virtual tie" now means win") and anything else they have to in order to sustain the status quo. 

Campaigns are psychological - and she dare not admit to the truth here. That's also why she and the aforementioned players are avoiding the truth as much as possible. Unfortunately for them, for literally THE FIRST TIME IN 40 YEARS - the citizens of our country refuse to be treated as mushrooms who "go along to get along." We're fed up and taking on one of the most massive status quo systems in history.

AN IMPORTANT POINT THAT ALL US REVOLUTIONARIES NEED TO KEEP IN MIND: the status quo system that the various entities are protecting is based on BILLIONS OF DOLLARS. 

The establishment set up a system to serve themselves, and they're going to have to be turned on their heads for us to succeed. 

The most glaring example of this is reflected in the fact that in these decades, APPROXIMATELY 97% OF OUR CONGRESS HAVE DONE WHAT HILLARY HAS - BECOME MEMBERS OF THE .01% OF THE WEALTHIEST IN OUR NATION. 

If you check, that is 180 degrees from where it was even 30 years ago. Back then, they were "public servants" whose salaries often forced a penurious life style in D.C. That's no longer the case.
